description:
Responsibilities


Analyze tenders and coorindate with respective stations and agents;
Set up RFQ pre-alignment call and final call with RFQ key stakeholders;
Convert customer rate file into internal rate file;
Being responsible for validating information and consolidation of pricing data for the RFQ submission;
Review RFQ pricing with key stakeholders;
Maintain tender data profiling and records;
perform any ad-hoc assignments when required.

Qualifications

Bachelor degree or above with at least 3 years of experiences in sales, pricing, RFQ, tender management or customer service in freight forwarding industry;
Familiar with worldwide markets;
Fluent in spoken and written English, and a local language;
Strong computer skills e.g. MS Excel pivot tables and formulas.

Interested parties, please send full resume, availability and expected salary to our Company.

All information provided by applicants will be treated in strict confidence and used only for employment-related purposes. All personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 6 months.

Job Descriptions:

Daily works include, but not limited to:

Support outdoor sales and teammates for sales related issues, not limited to rate inquiries or prepare quotations;
Prepare tailor-made shipments and invoices reports;
Shipment coordination and problem solving for the stakeholders;
Follow up invoice billing, chasing outstanding payment, and credit control.
Requirements:

Degree or above in any discipline;
Relevant freight forwarding experience is required;
Fluent in written and spoken English and Mandarin;
Proactive, good interpersonal and analytical skills.
Interested parties please send full resume with employment history and expected salary to HRA Division, Yusen Logistics (Hong Kong) Limited at Level 31, Tower 1, Kowloon Commerce Centre, 51 Kwai Cheong Road, Kwai Chung or by email to hr.ylhk@ hk.yusen-logistics.com .



Yusen Logistics (Hong Kong) is an equal opportunity employer. All information collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

“K” Line Logistics (Hong Kong) Limited is a global logistics company offering total logistics solution including air and ocean freight, land transport and distribution etc.  Our headquarters is based in Japan and our international network links more than 150 countries and cities worldwide. To cope with our expansion, we are inviting high caliber professional for the following position:

ASSISTANT ACCOUNTANT 
 
(Working location: Lai Chi Kok)

This position will be responsible to handle daily bank operations including payment & receipt vouchers as well as autopay arrangement, bank reconciliation, book-keeping, staff reimbursement. You are required to handle some ad hoc jobs.


Requirements:

Form 5 / DSE or above, Diploma or above in Accounting discipline;
LCCI higher / ACCA level 1 or above;
At least 1 year accounting experience in which exposure in freight forwarder industry is an advantage;
Good in spoken and written English and Chinese, Mandarin speaking is an advantage;
Good computer skills with MS Office, Flex Accounting is preferable;
Strong in communication and problem solving skills;
Detailed minded, reliable, self-motivated and team player;
Immediate available preferred

We offer attractive fringe benefits which include 5 days work-week, Double Pay, Performance Bonus, Training Allowances, Overtime Allowances, Medical & Dental Scheme, Mandatory Provident Fund and 12-21 days Annual Leave.

If you are interested in this position, please send application with detailed qualifications, experience, current and expected salary by click “Apply Now” to submit your application.

(All information provided are kept confidential and all personal data provided will be used for the recruitment purpose only)

Job Duties:


Follow up cargoes;
Prepare purchases & sales contracts;
Co-ordinate with suppliers, buyers & head office to arrange loading schedules;
Handle full set shipping documents & issue invoices, etc.
Fulfill other duties related to operations;

 
Requirement:


University graduate in Shipping Logistics and Global Supply Chain are highly preferred;

Proficiency in Mandarin, English and Chinese;
Self-motivated, Reliable, Independent, Team work, Detail-minded and able to work under pressure;
1 to 2 years working experience in operations and logistics;

Fresh graduate will be also considered;
Immediately Available.

*Interested parties, please send full resume with current & expected salary & date available in MS WORD FORMAT ONLY to email:  jobs@HKETERNITY. com    or fax to 3527 0634

Hotline: (852) 3542 5082

For more jobs, please visit our website: www.hketernity.com

We are welcome applicants resend resumes to us even you have applied jobs in our company before.

(Personal data submitted are for recruitment purpose only.)
